The purpose of the application test de- signed for this study was to determine whether there was a significant difference between the experimental and control sec- tions in their ability to utilize and apply meteorological information. The applica- tion test (reliability .So), employed the use of materials with which a pupil might come in daily contact. The material for the items was obtained from such sources as 2x2 color slides of cloud formations, articles with reference to weather found in current newspapers and popular periodicals, and weather forecast maps as illustrated in daily newspapers.

out_desc_tool: In the SSA /"instrument, the declarative knowledge items measure recall of the facts and concepts covered during instruction The procedural knowledge items measure the ability to utilize the process skills of data analysis for collecting, recording, displaying, etc., of data. These items generate data and require students to apply one or more process skills. Items on higher- thinking skills test the ability to analyze, interpret and explain data. The achievement level of each student was indicated by the sum of the scores for his/her correct responses.
